Comparing Four Measures of Codon Bias

Full set of genes: 1620 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level across 22 strains

Partial set of genes: 185 genes, each different at the nucleotide sequence level and identical at the amino acid sequence level across 22 strains

Split set of genes: 810 genes in each group (high/low medianPA)

03/15/2023

library(car)
library(lme4)
library(reshape2)

Figure 2A - Analysis of Codon Bias on the Full Set of Genes

Define the response variable.

response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1620_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)

Codon Adaptation Index (CAI) with Carbone Reference Set

Menu
Read in Data
explanatory0 <- read.csv('CAI_Carbone_1620_YRC_diff_d.csv')
explanatory0 <- melt(explanatory0, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "CAI")
dataset$CAI <- explanatory0$CAI
Summary Results of Mixed Model
lmm1 <- lmer(logPPR ~ CAI + (1+CAI|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))

Menu
Read in Data

Define the response variable.

response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1620_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)
explanatory0 <- read.csv('tAI_1620_YRC_diff_d.csv')
explanatory0 <- melt(explanatory0, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "tAI")
dataset$tAI <- explanatory0$tAI

#include median protein abundance for each gene

explanatory1 <- read.csv('PA_medians_1620.csv')
explanatory1 <- melt(explanatory1, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "medianPA")
dataset$medianPA = explanatory1$medianPA/10000

Summary Results of Model
lmm7 <- lmer(logPPR ~ tAI + (0+tAI|gene) + (1+tAI|medianPA), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="Nelder_Mead", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
summary(lmm7)

Fixed Effects Slope Significance Results
lmm8 <- lmer(logPPR ~ (0+tAI|gene) + (1+tAI|medianPA), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
tai1620m<-anova(lmm7, lmm8)

Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm7)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm7), res, col='yellowgreen', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$tAI, res, col='yellowgreen', span=0.1, xlab='tAI', ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='yellowgreen')
qqline(res)
